data.name: comboStandardType.ToolTip
data.value: The type to use as the internal standard, or the denominator in peak area ratios.

data.name: comboLabelType.ToolTip
data.value: The currently active isotope label type for which isotope modifications are being chosen.

data.name: listHeavyMods.ToolTip
data.value: Modifications applied to any of the heavy forms of the peptides, which are typically changes to the isotopic make-up of the molecules, with no impact on structure.

data.name: listStaticMods.ToolTip
data.value: Modifications applied to the light form of the peptides which are typically due to changes in the molecular structure of the peptide.

data.name: listStandardTypes.ToolTip
data.value: The types to use as internal standards, or the denominators in peak area ratios calculated for other types.

data.name: textMaxVariableMods.ToolTip
data.value: The maximum number of variable modifications allowed to occur in combination on any peptide instance.

data.name: textMaxNeutralLosses.ToolTip
data.value: The maximum number of neutral loss events allowed to occur in combination on any fragment instance.

data.name: comboMissedCleavages.ToolTip
data.value: The maximum number of missed cleavages allowed in a peptide when considering protein digestion.

data.name: comboEnzyme.ToolTip
data.value: The protease enzyme used for digesting proteins into peptides prior to injection into the mass spectrometer

data.name: comboBackgroundProteome.ToolTip
data.value: Processed FASTA sequence information specifying the full set of proteins that may be present in the sample matrix to be injected into the mass spectrometer.

data.name: textMeasureRTWindow.ToolTip
data.value: Time window in minutes around a measured peak center (i.e. (start + end)/2) used in scheduling future peptide measurements.

data.name: cbUseMeasuredRT.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, then previously measured retention times will be used to predict retention times for scheduling of future peptide measurements.

data.name: comboRetentionTime.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies a linear equation that may be used to predict retention times from a peptide specific hydrophobicity score.

data.name: cbAutoSelect.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, peptides are automatically chosen from proteins using specified filter and library settings. Otherwise, all peptide selection must be done by manual document editing.

data.name: textExcludeAAs.ToolTip
data.value: Exclude all peptides starting before this amino acid position in each protein

data.name: cbRaggedEnds.ToolTip
data.value: Exclude peptides resulting from cleavage sites with immediate preceding or following cleavage sites. e.g. RR, KK, RK, KR for trypsin

data.name: btnEditExlusions.ToolTip
data.value: Edit the list of available peptide exclusions

data.name: listboxExclusions.ToolTip
data.value: Regular expression patterns that may be used to exclude certain peptides

data.name: textMaxLength.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum number of amino acids allowed in peptides matching this filter

data.name: textMinLength.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum number of amino acids allowed in peptides matching this filter

data.name: btnExplore.ToolTip
data.value: Open the MS/MS spectral library explorer

data.name: btnBuildLibrary.ToolTip
data.value: Build a MS/MS spectral library from peptide search results from various peptide search engines.

data.name: comboRank.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies a value associated with each spectrum in a library that may be used to rank matching peptides. Not all library formats provide the same values for ranking.

data.name: textPeptideCount.ToolTip
data.value: The number of top ranking peptides to choose for each protein

data.name: comboMatching.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the peptide picking strategy: Library - picks only peptides that match a library spectrum Filter - ignores library contents for picking and uses the settings on the Filter tab instead Library and Filter - picks peptides that match both a library spectrum and the filter Library or Filter - picks peptides that match either a library spectrum or the filter

data.name: cbLimitPeptides.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, only a specified number of top ranking peptides are picked for each protein.

data.name: editLibraries.ToolTip
data.value: Edit the list of available MS/MS spectral libraries.

data.name: listLibraries.ToolTip
data.value:
The set of MS/MS spectral libraries matched with the peptides and transitions in the current document. These libraries may be used to rank and pick both peptides and transitions in the document.
Library spectra are automatically matched in the order they appear in this list, with light spectra matched first, followed by isotope labeled spectra in the order the label types are listed in the modifications tab.

data.name: comboPeakScoringModel.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies a linear equation that may be used to predict retention times from a peptide specific hydrophobicity score.

data.name: comboBoxPeptideUniquenessConstraint.ToolTip
data.value: "Protein" excludes any peptide that appears in more than one protein in the background proteome. "Gene" excludes any peptide that appears in proteins for more than one gene in the background proteome. "Species" excludes any peptide that appears in proteins for more than one species in the background proteome.

data.name: btnFilter.ToolTip
data.value: Filter a MS/MS spectral library from a MIDAS library

data.name: tbxMaxLoqBias.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum bias or difference from the known concentration allowed for the model estimate based on measured area of the concentration designated as the lower limit of quantification (LOQ)

data.name: comboLodMethod.ToolTip
data.value: Method of determining the lower limit of detection (LOD)

data.name: tbxMaxLoqCv.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum CV allowed among multiple meassurements of the concentration designated as the lower limit of quantification (LOQ)

data.name: tbxQuantUnits.ToolTip
data.value: Units to be applied to calibrated quantities

data.name: comboQuantMsLevel.ToolTip
data.value: Mass spectrum level (1, 2 or both) used to quantify

data.name: comboNormalizationMethod.ToolTip
data.value: Method used to normalize peak areas across runs

data.name: comboRegressionFit.ToolTip
data.value: Regression model used to estimate the relationship between peak area and quantitative values

data.name: comboWeighting.ToolTip
data.value: The equation used to weight the impact of points in calculating the regression
